@page "/"
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]

<PageMeta Title="ScamAlert — watch over the PCs your family uses"
          Description="ScamAlert helps you protect loved ones by alerting trusted family when suspicious remote access hits their Windows PC."
          CanonicalPath="/" />

<section class="hero-sa mb-5">
    <div class="row g-4 align-items-center">
        <div class="col-lg-7">
            <p class="text-uppercase small fw-semibold text-sa-accent mb-2">Family remote-access protection</p>
            <h1 class="display-6 fw-semibold mb-3">You cannot sit at every keyboard. ScamAlert helps you watch the ones that matter.</h1>
            <p class="lead text-secondary">
                Install protection on a parent’s PC, a grandparent’s laptop, or your teen’s computer. When someone tries to
                reach that machine over remote desktop or similar paths, <strong>your family gets the alert</strong>—not a stranger in a call center.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-3"><span class="badge rounded-pill text-bg-light border">$7.99/month · one simple plan</span></p>
            <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-2">
                <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="/signup">Protect someone I love</a>
                <a class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-lg" href="/pricing">See pricing</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-5">
            <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm hero-card">
                <div class="card-body p-4">
                    <h2 class="h5 mb-3">Built for families, not IT departments</h2>
                    <ul class="mb-0 text-secondary sa-checklist">
                        <li>Watch inbound RDP, SSH, and Telnet on the PCs you name</li>
                        <li>Text the people <em>you</em> trust—spouse, adult child, sibling</li>
                        <li>Stop “surprise” remote sessions during refund and tech-support scams</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="mb-5">
    <h2 class="h4 mb-4 text-center">Who you are protecting</h2>
    <div class="row g-3">
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h3 class="h6">Parents &amp; grandparents</h3>
                    <p class="small text-secondary mb-0">They may not recognize a scammer on the phone asking them to install remote software. You still get notified when access is attempted.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h3 class="h6">Teens &amp; young adults</h3>
                    <p class="small text-secondary mb-0">Their machine can be targeted too. A trusted adult on the account can respond when something looks wrong.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h3 class="h6">Anyone you worry about</h3>
                    <p class="small text-secondary mb-0">One account, trusted contacts, and clear alerts—so distance does not mean silence.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="mb-5 py-4 px-3 rounded sa-muted-panel">
    <h2 class="h4 mb-4">How ScamAlert helps you watch</h2>
    <div class="row g-4">
        <div class="col-md-4 text-center">
            <div class="step-num">1</div>
            <h3 class="h6">Install on their PC</h3>
            <p class="small text-secondary">Lightweight Windows protection on the computer you want to watch.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4 text-center">
            <div class="step-num">2</div>
            <h3 class="h6">Name your trusted contacts</h3>
            <p class="small text-secondary">Choose who gets SMS—usually you and another family member.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4 text-center">
            <div class="step-num">3</div>
            <h3 class="h6">Get alerted together</h3>
            <p class="small text-secondary">Suspicious remote access triggers texts so your family can call back and intervene.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <p class="text-center mb-0 mt-3">
        <a href="/how-it-works">Full walkthrough</a> · <a href="/pricing">$7.99/month plan</a>
    </p>
</section>

<section class="text-center mb-4">
    <h2 class="h4 mb-2">Peace of mind when you cannot be in the room</h2>
    <p class="text-secondary col-lg-8 mx-auto">
        ScamAlert does not replace talking to your loved ones about scams—it adds a safety net when criminals push remote access anyway.
    </p>
    <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/signup">Start protecting my family</a>
</section>
